SIMPLE: mordant
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mordant
<hw>Mor"dant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p. pr. of
<ets>mordere</ets> to bite; L. <ets>mordere</ets>. See
<er>Morsel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Biting; caustic; sarcastic;
keen; severe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Dyeing & Calico Printing)</fld> <def>Serving to fix
colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mordant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mordant
<hw>Mor"dant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., originally, biting.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any corroding substance used in etching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Dyeing & Calico Printing)</fld> <def>Any substance,
as alum or copperas, which, having a twofold attraction for organic
fibers and coloring matter, serves as a bond of union, and thus gives
fixity to, or <xex>bites in</xex>, the dyes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Gilding)</fld> <def>Any sticky matter by which the
gold leaf is made to adhere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mordant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mordant
<hw>Mor"dant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Mordanted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mordanting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To subject to the action of,
or imbue with, a mordant; <as>as, to <ex>mordant</ex> goods for
dyeing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mordantly</ent>⟦br⟧
